$ Business continuity

{ Two metrics

  { Recovery Point Objective (RPO)

    The RPO is the amount of â†’ development/Data, measured in a time-duration, that an organization is prepared to tolarete loosing.

    In order to achieve an RPO of say 12 hours, the data needs to be backed up and replicated in intervals that are no longer than 12 hours.

  }
  { Recovery Time Object (RTO)
  
    The RTO is the duration of time that the organization is willing to wait after a disaster happened until the data is restored again and productivity can be resumed.

  }

